                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><date>Wednesday, 17th of Hesvan (Nov), 1865</date>.</p>\n            <p>Peace and all good forever:</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">To this day I am without a word from you. My low spirits\n                in-<lb/>crease from day to day. Herewith you will receive the beautiful article<lb/>\n                about which you must certainly be thinking and in which my honest prin-<lb/>ciples\n                are expressed.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You would be doing a great kindness if you could print it<lb/> also\n                in German with English letters, but in any case it must be transla-<lb/>ted. Perhaps\n                you would have printed several hundred copies of the article<lb/> as a circular, in\n                order that it might be more widely spread over the land.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I feel very unhappy here. I have the notion to have my<lb/>\n                    “<persName>Esther</persName>” printed there and to stay there during the\n                printing, and give<lb/> there lectures about history and religion. That should bring\n                something<lb/> in. In this way I could support and encourage your efforts with\n                regard<lb/> to the seminary. The honor belongs to you. I had enough of it at\n                home.<lb/> Here it is a case of “He who increases knowledge increases pain”.\n                Here<lb/> one must be either a <persName>Wise</persName> or, on the other hand, an\n                    <persName>Illoway</persName>. Both of them<lb/> “This one as he understands it\n                and this one as he understands it”, but<lb/> they are alike in character.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I tell you this idea in secret, and if you agree, I shall<lb/> write\n                to <persName>Weiler</persName> and <persName>Ellis</persName>...... I must work\n                openly, otherwise I shall<lb/> be destroyed , God forbid, As a friend of six years'\n                standing, you owe<lb/> it to me who never changed his word, just as you owe it to me\n                who never changed his word, just as you owe it to the Torah<lb/> that is in me, to\n                do everything possible. “A prisoner cannot release<lb/> himself from the\n                prison”.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">As soon as you have translated the article, I want the<lb/>\n                manuscript. I should also very much like to see the proof sheet of<lb/> the English.\n                The matter is too important. A word incorrectly put<lb/> may be injurious.</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z60cn76/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
